The paper discusses methods for analyzing principal components in discrete data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper also mentions applications in text prediction and information retrieval, which are subfields of natural language processing and information retrieval, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
